ZCZC GE23
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 202300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING LOW 997 WILL BE CENTRED OVER THE WERN N
SEA WITH A RIDGE ACROSS SWERN PARTS OF THE BRITISH ISLES.
ON MONDAY THE LOW IS EXP TO MOV SE INTO NERN GERMANY AND
FILL WITH A RIDGE BLDN IN THE NE OF THE CULLERCOATS
AREA BUT WITH FRONTAL TROUGHS BRINGING A MORE CYCLONIC
FLOW TO THE W. DURING TUESDAY THE CYCLONIC FLOW IS EXP TO
SPREAD E TO MOST PARTS OF THE FCST AREA WITH CURRENT
EXPECTATIONS FOR THIS TO PERSIST IN THE N ON WEDNESDAY
BUT WITH A TRANSIENT RIDGE MOV E THROUGH SERN PARTS. NEAR
GALE TO GALE FORCE WINDS IN THE NEERN AND SERN N SEA AND
ENGLISH CHANNEL ON SUNDAY EVENING WILL MOD THROUGH MONDAY
MORNING. WIDESPREAD GALES THEN EXP IN THE NERN N SEA
OVERNIGHT MONDAY AND INTO TUESDAY MORNING THESE THEN
CURRENTLY FCST TO BE CONFINED TO THE FAR NE OF
CULLERCOATS BY LATE TUESDAY AND MOD BY WEDNESDAY MORNING
